Package com.clarisma.common.parser

Class Parser

java.lang.Object
com.clarisma.common.parser.Parser
All Implemented Interfaces:
FileLocation, CharSequence
Direct Known Subclasses:
JsonParser, MatcherParser, TagsParser
public class Parser extends Object implements CharSequence, FileLocation
An extendable general-purpose lexer/parser, especially suited for generating abstract syntax trees.

    • initialCharTokens

      protected short[] initialCharTokens
      An index to speed up token matching: each array position represents an ASCII character (0-127) and contains the index of the last string in `tokenStrings` that begins with this character (built once actual parsing starts). Matching always starts with the last entry in `tokenStrings` and works backwards, in order to match the longest possible sequence. This way, ">=" is matched before ">", since it appears later in the alphabetically ordered list.

    • identifierPattern

      protected Pattern identifierPattern
      A regex pattern used to match identifiers

  • Method Details

    • addToken

      public void addToken(String string, Object token, boolean replace)
      Adds a string and its corresponding token (which can be the string itself) to the lexer table. This method must be called before parsing starts. Unless `replace` is `true`, an exception is thrown if a token already exists for the given string. Multiple strings can produce the same token.
      Parameters:
      string - the string the lexer should match ...
      token - ... and the token to be produced
      replace - If `true`, any previous string/token association will be replaced

    • parse

      public void parse(CharSequence s)
      Starts the parsing process for the given character sequence. Initializes the lexer and moves to the first non-whitespace token. To consume tokens and turn them into production elements, call the appropriate production methods of the parser subclass for the grammar to be parsed.
      Parameters:
      s - the character sequence to be parsed
